description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a full time, highly committed, motivated and conscientious Registered Pharmacy Technician to help develop the Pharmacy Service at Glangwili General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is suitable for both newly qualified Technicians/experienced Technicians or someone who would like to experience Hospital Pharmacy for the first time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must possess excellent communication skills and be able to work as part of a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glangwili General Hospital is a busy District General Hospital with approximately 420 beds. It provides a range of medical and surgical specialities including coronary care, acute stoke, respiratory, urology, trauma &amp; orthopaedics, obstetrics &amp; gynaecology, critical care and paediatrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Pharmacy Department has undergone major refurbishment including the installation of a new automated dispensing system. The Department also provides a comprehensive medicines management service to all wards and uses the All Wales electronic discharge system (MTeD).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will perform a range of activities working in various sections of the department, including working as part of our ward based clinical pharmacy teams and supporting the various functions in the dispensary. You must be able to work in a busy and demanding working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you have a Level 3 BTEC/NVQ Pharmacy Services Certificate or equivalent and MUST be registered with the General Pharmaceutical Council as a Pharmacy Technician. &lt;strong&gt;Applicants who do not hold this registration will not be shortlisted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full &amp; Part time hours considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in the post please contact Sally Davey, Senior Pharmacy Technician on 01267 227469 for an informal discussion or to arrange a departmental visit.&lt;/p&gt;
